For measurement of the dry cell weight, cellulose nitrate membrane filters with a 0.45 μm pore size (Whatman, USA) were pre-dried in an oven at 80 °C. Suspensions of N. gaditana were passed through the filters using a vacuum pump, and then the filters were dried at 80 °C overnight. The dry cell weight was determined as follows:Dry cell weight=weight after filtration-(weight before filtration)volume of filtration\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
