				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\mu = \frac{{\ln X_{2} - \ln X_{1} }}{{t_{2} - t_{1} }}$$\end{document}where t is time and Xi is the dry cell weight of N. gaditana at time ti.

Lipid content was analyzed using the modified Folch method [33]. Suspensions of N. gaditana were harvested and centrifuged at 7000 rpm for 10 min. The harvested pellets were washed twice using distilled water and then stored at − 70 °C for 24 h. The frozen cells were freeze-dried (Ilshin, Republic of Korea) for 4 days and then ground into fine powders. They were treated with a solution of chloroform/methanol (2:1, v/v) to extract lipids. Phase separation was achieved by adding water, followed by centrifugation at 4000 rpm for 10 min. The lower phase was handled with a syringe, and left overnight to evaporate remaining solvents. The total lipid content was calculated as follows:Total lipid content\%,g oil g biomass-1=(WL-WD)×VCVP×WS×100\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {\text{Total lipid content }}\left( {{\text{\%}}, {\text{g oil g biomass}}^{ - 1} } \right) = \frac{{(W_{\text{L}} - W_{\text{D}} ) \times V_{\text{C}} }}{{V_{\text{P}} \times W_{\text{S}} }} \times 100 $$\end{document}where WL is the weight of the dish containing the lipid sample, WD is the weight of the dish, WS is the weight of dry biomass, VC is the added volume of chloroform, and VP is the volume of chloroform moved to the dish.

To measure ash content in dry biomass, an aluminum dish was pre-burned in a furnace at 575 °C for 3 h and then the weight of the burned dish was measured. The weight of the dry biomass sample was measured afterwards, and then the dish containing the biomass was burned in the furnace at the same conditions mentioned above. The final ash content was calculated as follows:Ash content\%,g g biomass-1=W3-W1W2-W1×100\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text{Ash content }}\left( {{\text{\%}}, {\text{g g biomass}}^{ - 1} } \right) = \frac{{W_{3} - W_{1} }}{{W_{2} - W_{1} }} \times 100$$\end{document}where W1 is the weight of the burned dish, W2 is the weight of the dish with dry biomass, and W3 is the weight of the burned dish containing burned biomass.

Protein content was presented as follows:Protein content\%,g g biomass-1=100-Clipid-Ccarbohydrate-Cash\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
